# TryHackMe – Day 2 Notes (Networking Basics)

## Room Focus
Networking fundamentals + Linux command line basics

---

## Topics Covered
- IP addressing
- Subnetting basics (CIDR)
- Network ranges
- File system navigation
- Permissions
- Common Linux commands

---

## Commands Practiced

### File navigation
pwd
ls
cd

### File search
grep

### Permissions
chmod

### Network testing
ping
ifconfig / ipconfig
traceroute

---

## Key Lessons Learned

1. Networking is foundational for cybersecurity
   Without understanding IPs and subnets, scanning and enumeration are confusing.

2. Don’t memorize commands
   Understanding what each command does makes troubleshooting easier.

3. Practice > theory
   Hands-on labs helped more than reading alone.

---

## Challenges Faced
- Subnetting calculations were confusing at first
- Remembering CIDR notation took practice

---

